==Starting out==
* '''Brother Aimeri:''' Nilsal, traveller. I was injured while exploring down here. Could you spare me some cooked fish, meat or vegetables?
* {{tcond|If the player has food in inventory:}}
** '''Player:''' It just so happens that I have some with me!
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' Oh, please hand it over if you can spare it.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has no food in inventory:}}
** '''Player:''' I'm afraid that I don't have any of that type of food with me.
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' Oh, well if you return with any I would greatly appreciate it.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If player uses anything other than food on him:}}
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' No thanks. I would rather eat fish, meat or vegetables.
** {{tact|end}}

===After healing Brother Aimeri===
* '''Brother Aimeri:''' Thanks for helping me. Is there anything you'd like to know about this temple? If you find anything in here, show it to me and I'll tell you what I know about it.
* {{topt|What is this place?}}
** '''Player:''' What is this place?
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' This place probably had a name at some point but it has long since been forgotten. The Arceuus librarians refer to this place as the Forthos Dungeon.
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' It is rumoured that this place used to be of religious significance to druidic followers of both Ralos and Ranul.
** '''Player:''' Who are Ralos and Ranul?
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' According to religious texts, Ralos is the god of the sun and Ranul, his brother, is the god of the moon.
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' If you find any artifacts or relics from within this temple, I would be very interested in seeing them.
** '''Player:''' I'll see what I find. Although, I've never heard of Ralos and Ranul.
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' You need only to look up and see their greatness above you when you return to the surface.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Who are you?}}
** '''Player:''' Who are you?
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' My name is Brother Aimeri, I am a travelling monk from the distant land of Varlamore on a journey to uncover the secrets of this temple.
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' I worship Ralos, a common practice where I am from. However, I found out that our order may have originated from this temple. If you find anything of interest, please let me know.
** '''Player:''' I'll keep my eyes open.
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' You have my gratitude. Any information you do find would also be of interest to the Arceuus Library. I hope we can uncover the secrets of this place for the greater good.
** '''Player:''' The greater good.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|How did you get injured?}}
** '''Player:''' How did you get injured?
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' I found out about this place from Logosia in the Arceuus Library. I came to investigate but was ambushed by the spiders in the room to the north.
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' I'm a scholar not a fighter. I didn't have time to think through my options so I did what came naturally and ran away.
** '''Player:''' Why didn't you decide to run back the way you came from instead of running further into the dungeon where there could be more dangerous creatures?
** '''Brother Aimeri:''' See, the problem with that... Is that it is an excellent idea I wish I had thought of at the time.
** '''Player:''' You've been trapped here for a while! No wonder you were hungry!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|quest=no|Ask about the cursed altar.}}
* {{topt|quest=no|Ask about the Temple Key}}
* {{topt|I'm fine, thanks.}}
** '''Player:''' I'm fine, thanks.
** {{tact|end}}

